(window["webpackJsonp"]=window["webpackJsonp"]||[]).push([["about"],{"1a18":function(a,t,e){"use strict";e("8cba")},"8cba":function(a,t,e){},f820:function(a,t,e){"use strict";e.r(t);var n=e("7a23"),o=Object(n["F"])("data-v-349d2d30");Object(n["t"])("data-v-349d2d30");var d={class:"about"},s=Object(n["f"])('<h1 data-v-349d2d30>Translate helper tool</h1> Local-only web tool to help keeping track of and updating translations scratchbook as you work. <h2 data-v-349d2d30>Setup</h2><p data-v-349d2d30>In settings, set up the following:</p><ul data-v-349d2d30><li data-v-349d2d30><strong data-v-349d2d30>Filename</strong> - filename template you&#39;ll get when exporting translations. Use <pre data-v-349d2d30>{name}</pre> as placeholder for name you&#39;ll type when exporting. </li><li data-v-349d2d30><strong data-v-349d2d30>Languages</strong> - list of languages for translations. Languages will be used as keys for translations provided </li><li data-v-349d2d30><strong data-v-349d2d30>Translation prefix</strong> - constant that will be put in translation file before all translations. Useful for making translation SQLs etc. </li><li data-v-349d2d30><strong data-v-349d2d30>Translation suffix</strong> - constant that will be put in translation file after all translations. Useful for making translation SQLs etc. </li><li data-v-349d2d30><strong data-v-349d2d30>Translation entry</strong> - single entry, one per each language of each translation. Can be templated with <pre data-v-349d2d30>{lang}</pre> for language, <pre data-v-349d2d30>{key}</pre> for translation key and <pre data-v-349d2d30>{value}</pre> for translated text. </li><li data-v-349d2d30><strong data-v-349d2d30>Translation sources</strong> - optional, URL to translations JSON (a JSON that keeps translations as JSON object, with dot-path allowing to access nodes/leafs), to check whether newly added translations conflict with existing ones. Downloaded translations are cached locally in browser, and are refreshed every time you load page or save settings. </li></ul><h2 data-v-349d2d30>Usage</h2><p data-v-349d2d30> Plus button adds new translations row, if there&#39;s no empty row visible. Empty row should add automatically at the end as you add translations. </p><p data-v-349d2d30> Cloud button prepares generating translations export - after providing translation name (used as template in filename defined in settings), click Download to get translation file downloaded. </p><p data-v-349d2d30> X button clears translation list. <strong data-v-349d2d30>There is no confirmation!</strong></p><p data-v-349d2d30> Translations are automatically being saves as you type, in your browser&#39;s local storage, if you want to come back to them later. Settings need to be saved manually. </p><h2 data-v-349d2d30>Privacy</h2><p data-v-349d2d30> All data are stored locally, using browser&#39;s local storage for page. No data is being sent or uploaded anywhere, there&#39;s no tracking on the site. All code is available open source <a href="https://github.com/asmnh/translate-helper" target="_blank" data-v-349d2d30>on Github</a>, including build process. </p>',12);Object(n["r"])();var l=o((function(a,t){return Object(n["q"])(),Object(n["d"])("div",d,[s])}));e("1a18");const r={};r.render=l,r.__scopeId="data-v-349d2d30";t["default"]=r}}]);
